{"TopicId":160280,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Is there an Odometer?","CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T21:37:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T21:37:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone know of a mod that adds an odometer to a wheeled vehicle? Or some other way to determine distance covered across the ground?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StupidAndy","CreatedById":171175,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T21:57:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe velocity measurer on the navball displays horizontal velocity, that\u0027s basically an odometer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SchwinnTropius","CreatedById":165170,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T21:59:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure there is one, and I\u0027m not sure how well it would work. Any time you launch a wheeled vehicle, it comes with brand new parts as if straight off the assembly line (probably was), and then it\u0027s recovered and recycled. Maybe for a vehicle in one flight, it would be cool to track distance travelled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T22:48:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223047430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160280\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494107824\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022171175\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StupidAndy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, StupidAndy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe velocity measurer on the navball displays horizontal velocity, that\u0027s basically an odometer\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would call that a speedometer, since it is measuring current speed whereas\u00A0An odometer measures distance travelled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Urses","CreatedById":175990,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T22:58:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150244-nightside/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150244\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150244-nightside/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nightside\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry with the F3. Distance covered over ground tab maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr try with Waypoint Manager. You can can see airline from your vehicle for a specific waypoint.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny Kabooms\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUrses\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-06T23:01:08Z\u0022 title=\u002205/06/2017 11:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 6, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Urses\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StupidAndy","CreatedById":171175,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T23:12:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223047481\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160280\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494110908\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would call that a speedometer, since it is measuring current speed whereas\u00A0An odometer measures distance travelled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince I know nothing about cars I wouldn\u0027t really know that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou can put a flag where you start, and see how far away it is at the end, but that only works with a straight line...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Waxing_Kibbous","CreatedById":151611,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-07T00:10:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool idea, it would be handy for mods where stuff breaks also \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-07T14:20:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know RoverScience tracks how far you\u0027ve gone on a planet - you might check with them on how they do it. \u00A0(Though I suspect it\u0027s \u0027straight-line from first landed point\u0027.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-07T15:03:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ll be wanting \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/45314-102-persistent-trails-record-share-and-replay-track-data-may-14-v12/\u0026amp;do=findComment\u0026amp;comment=2808687\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPersistent Trails\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-08T05:22:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=